question: Who has won the 2017 under-15 girls Dutch Open Junior Squash Championship?
explanation: Ananya Dabke from India has won the under-15 girl title at the Dutch Open Junior Squash Championship by defeating Serena Daniel of the US in the final by 11-7, 11-4, 12-10 in Amsterdam, Netherlands. Apart from this, the top seeded Neel Joshi  bagged the under-15 boys title in the tournament by defeating  5/8 seed Khalil Alhassan of England in the final by 9-11, 11-4, 11-5, 11-6.
